  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Abby Kelley Foster expresses her sorrow at learning that Maria Weston Chapman&apos;s husband [Henry Grafton Chapman] is ill again. She urges Maria to come to the Millbury fair knowing that H. G. Chapman&apos;s illness will probably prevent her from attending. She wishes that Mary Chapman, Ann T. G. Phillips, and other Boston abolitionists would also come to the fair.</subfield>
